    "body": "Add a unified merge_state API, which can automatically fallback to the Triton kernel in some cases (e.g., for AMD GPUs, when the head dimension is not a multiple of 4 or 8, and in FP8 precision). This PR should not be merged until #5419 is ready.\r\n\r\n## w/ this PR and flashinfer backend\r\n\r\n- launch cmd\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython3 -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n  --model $HF_MODELS/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct \\\r\n  --trust-remote-code \\\r\n  --tp-size 2 \\\r\n  --mem-fraction-static 0.9 \\\r\n  --attention-backend flashinfer \\\r\n  --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8852 \\\r\n  --dtype bfloat16\r\n```\r\n\r\n- gsm8k benchmark\r\n\r\nTest passed on NVIDIA L20 device.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py \\\r\n  --port 8852 --num-shots 8 \\\r\n  --num-questions 128 \\\r\n  --parallel 16 \\\r\n  --data-path /workspace/dev/openllm/benchmarks/data/gsm8k/test.jsonl\r\n100%|███████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 128/128 [00:16<00:00,  7.87it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.805\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 16.543 s\r\nOutput throughput: 754.076 token/s\r\n```\r\n\r\nsome debug log:\r\n```bash\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\n[2025-04-16 10:00:42 TP0] Prefill batch. #new-seq: 6, #new-token: 391, #cached-token: 7454, token usage: 0.00, #running-req: 10, #queue-req: 0,\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\nUse custom merge_state v2 CUDA kernel\r\n```",
